t4311.text: Though, I do share the same concerns, such as the cruelties meted out by Indian security forces against Muslims across India and people of Kashmir, the plight of Palestinians, difficulty of Burmese Rohingyas, conflict in Yemen and Syria. 14/15

t4312.text: It is always convenient by our leaders and Ministers to talk about the track record of foreign nations, in particular India of their human rights issues and ignore in-house state of affairs. 13/15

t4313.text: We, #Ahmadis, have been at the receiving end of intimidation, mob violence, demolition of worship places, destruction of businesses, societal discrimination and murders in Pakistan abetted by govt. Dr @ShireenMazari1 hasn’t uttered a word let alone taken actions. 12/15

t4314.text: Dr @ShireenMazari1 runs the portfolio of Human Rights ministry. In ordinary circumstances, this may sound strange for a government to establish such a ministry. But in Pakistani context it is necessary. 11/15

t4315.text: As an #Ahmadi of Pakistani origin, I had welcomed his government and expected some improvements & progress of the nation during his tenure. He has disappointed me so far. 10/15

t4316.text: @ImranKhanPTI was elected as the Prime Minister of all Pakistanis. He had invoked inspirational sentiments among everyday Pakistanis both inside the country and outside. He is vocal about Indian atrocities against Muslims but completely silent on #Ahmadi issues. 9/15

t4317.text: This environment has a very serious impact on the day to day lives of #Ahmadis in #Pakistan who otherwise are as ordinary citizens of the country as anyone else could be; working hard across all professions to put daily bread and butter on their tables. 8/15

t4318.text: The leaders from all persuasions, government & opposition, use religion for their political gains. #Ahmadis are singled out by most leaders who utter vile and hateful statements against the community and implore animosity. 7/15

t4319.text: The society has been radicalised in the past four decades. There is hate spewed against #Ahmadis day in and day out without giving any occasion for them to counter it or provide a rational rebuttal on any media. 6/15

t4320.text: The oppression against #Ahmadis is not an imaginative phenomenon. The hateful incitements by religious clergy and the anti-Ahmadi laws create an atmosphere of coercion against Ahmadis. 5/15

t4321.text: The hateful incitements by religious clerics rile up sections of society who take law into their own hands or get assistance by Police (in particular Punjab) and try to enforce vigilante justice by burning #Ahmadi mosques, businesses and houses. 4/15

t4322.text: It is worth noting that in many parts of the country, particularly in Punjab, #Ahmadis are pursued on petty issues on the pretext of violating Pakistan Penal Code 298 B & C. t4323.text: It will be #Pakistan’s gain to re-think the hateful religiosity and rather engage in quest for a fairer society for all sections of the nation. 2/15
